Noun
diva (plural divas)

literally means "goddess"

#1 (Opera) The principal female singer of an opera company, or opera star. 
#2 (Dance) A prima ballerina. 
#3 In popular music circles, diva has come to mean any celebrity, usually a well known singer. 
#4 A prima donna. (negative sense)  A person who considers himself or herself much more important than others, has high expectations of others and becomes angry when their standards or demands are not met.